back\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">März 21, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rsb1665702757952.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rsb1665702757952.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rsb1665702757952.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rsb1665702757952\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rsb1665702757952__lineardate_304794\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface data type that holds an integer representing a number of days.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"rsb1665702757952__topic_d92633e1_d92634e1_d92635e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rsb1665702757952__p_d92636e1_d92637e1_d92638e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lineardate</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ParamName</var>\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">:</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Direction</var>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rsb1665702757952__p_d92639e1_d92640e1_d92641e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">lineardate</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">VariableName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rsb1665702757952__topic_d61652e1_d61653e1_d61654e1_d61655e1_d61656e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d111538e83\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rsb1665702757952__d5970e20\">Use in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">params</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">variables</span> blocks to define the data type of a parameter or variable. The data type can be selected when defining fields, global variables, and component variables.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rsb1665702757952__topic_d61657e1_d61658e1_d61659e1_d61660e1_d61661e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d111538e98\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rsb1665702757952__p_d92651e1_d92652e1_d92653e1\">A <code class=\"ph codeph\">lineardate</code> can have a value from <code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code> (days) through <code class=\"ph codeph\">3652425</code> (10,000 years, that is, 3,652,425 days). Only a whole number of days is allowed; that is, you cannot specify hours, minutes and so on.</p>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">params\n date pContractDate : IN\n date pExecutionDate : IN\n lineardate pWaitPeriod : OUT\nendparams\npWaitPeriod = pExecutionDate - pContractDate</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vee1714313798310.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Handling in ProcScript</a><p>The ProcScript language enables you to convert data from one type to another, perform arithmetic operations, extract data values, and perform string substitution. Uniface carries out implicit type conversion whenever necessary, for example, when assignments are made between non-matching data types or when comparing non-matching data types. The ProcScript language also provides a number of functions that allow you to convert from one data type to another.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bcj1665702757168.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Date and Time Data</a><p>Uniface offers a wide variety of data types for date and time values.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nbc1665702757240.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Packing Codes for Date and Time Data</a><p>Uniface data types Date, Time, and Datetime (and linear variations of these) are associated with a variety of packing codes.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531760\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531760\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "lineardate Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 21, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface data type that holds an integer representing a number of days. lineardate ParamName : Direction lineardate VariableName Use Use in params and variables blocks to define the data type of a parameter or variable. The data type can be selected when defining fields, global variables, and component variables. Description A lineardate can have a value from 0 (days) through 3652425 (10,000 years, that is, 3,652,425 days). Only a whole number of days is allowed; that is, you cannot specify hours, minutes and so on. params date pContractDate : IN date pExecutionDate : IN lineardate pWaitPeriod : OUT endparams pWaitPeriod = pExecutionDate - pContractDate Copy Related Links Data Handling in ProcScript The ProcScript language enables you to convert data from one type to another, perform arithmetic operations, extract data values, and perform string substitution. Uniface carries out implicit type conversion whenever necessary, for example, when assignments are made between non-matching data types or when comparing non-matching data types. The ProcScript language also provides a number of functions that allow you to convert from one data type to another. Date and Time Data Uniface offers a wide variety of data types for date and time values. Packing Codes for Date and Time Data Uniface data types Date, Time, and Datetime (and linear variations of these) are associated with a variety of packing codes. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}